User: How do I üìã page meta enhancements in nuxt-blog?

Assistant: To üìã page meta enhancements in nuxt-blog, here's what you do:
We now support extracting extra page meta keys (likely used by module authors) via `experimental.extraPageMetaExtractionKeys`. This enables module authors to use this information at build time, in the `pages:resolved` hook.

We also now support local functions in `definePageMeta`. This means you can do something like this:

function validateIdParam(route) {
  return !!(route.params.id && !isNaN(Number(route.params.id)))
}

definePageMeta({
  validate: validateIdParam,
}).
Pretty straightforward, right?

